        <prompt>What was the 15th Amendment's primary purpose?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Guaranteed voting rights regardless of race</option>
            <option letter="b">Established citizenship rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Abolished slavery</option>
            <option letter="d">Created public education</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The 15th Amendment, ratified in 1870, prohibited denying voting rights based on race, color, or previous condition of servitude.</explanation>
